      "bug_description": "Isolated free cell (degree 0) is incorrectly marked as forceable. The algorithm treats any cell with non‑forceable neighbor count ≤ 1 as forceable, but a cell with no free neighbours cannot ever be forced to the lab because the robot cannot move.",
      "verdict": "FALSE_POSITIVE",
      "reasoning": "The propagation algorithm starts the BFS only from the lab cell. A cell becomes aforceable\" only when one of its neighbours is already known to be forceable and its remaining non‑forceable neighbour count drops to ≤ 1. An isolated free cell has degree 0 and no neighbours, so it is never reached by the BFS and never gets marked. Therefore the algorithm does NOT incorrectly mark isolated cells as forceable."
    },
    {
      "bug_description": "Free cell that belongs to a completely disconnected component (no path to the lab) is incorrectly marked as forceable. The current condition `non_forceable ≤ 1` is satisfied for a degree‑1 cell even when none of its neighbours are already known to be forceable, leading to false positives.",
      "verdict": "FALSE_POSITIVE",
      "reasoning": "Cells are only enqueued when a neighbour becomes forceable and the cell's non‑forceable neighbour count falls to ≤ 1. In a disconnected component none of the cells ever have a neighbour that is forceable (the lab is unreachable), so their counts never get decremented and they are never added to the queue. Consequently such cells remain unmarked, which is the correct behaviour."
    }
